WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:11.440 --> 00:00:14.230
- So those that have
seen bicep curl videos

00:00:14.230 --> 00:00:19.030
or bicep curl pictures
know that we recommend

00:00:19.030 --> 00:00:23.930
a very different type of curl than others.

00:00:23.930 --> 00:00:25.170
Now, I do want to say before we get into

00:00:25.170 --> 00:00:26.810
the curl discussion there's some people

00:00:26.810 --> 00:00:29.445
who just don't do curls because they

00:00:29.445 --> 00:00:32.930
really want to focus on
multi-joint movements

00:00:32.930 --> 00:00:35.267
or more functional
movements, which is a very

00:00:35.267 --> 00:00:38.330
over-used term. I mean,
the function of a muscle

00:00:38.330 --> 00:00:41.233
is to shorten, so you can
define anything as functional.

00:00:42.080 --> 00:00:44.970
But, they want to mimic the
things that they might do

00:00:44.970 --> 00:00:49.750
in a sport, or, you know,
maybe they want to do things

00:00:49.750 --> 00:00:53.750
that are called functional
by their CrossFit instructor

00:00:53.750 --> 00:00:58.230
which may or may not be
true. So, let's move on

00:00:58.230 --> 00:01:03.230
to the way we do curls. Now,
instead of a normal curl

00:01:03.560 --> 00:01:08.560
position, so, a normal curl
position finishes like this.

00:01:08.910 --> 00:01:12.738
You bring the bar almost up
to the bridge of your nose.

00:01:12.738 --> 00:01:16.680
The problem with bringing
the bar right here

00:01:16.680 --> 00:01:19.000
is if you look at the radius and ulna,

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:22.930
if you look at the lower
arm, it's perpendicular

00:01:22.930 --> 00:01:25.300
to the ground. This is not the ground.

00:01:25.300 --> 00:01:26.810
I know that, but, you know, the table's

00:01:26.810 --> 00:01:28.860
perpendicular, or parallel to the ground.

00:01:30.156 --> 00:01:33.567
So, when this happens,
the bicep is shut off.

00:01:34.520 --> 00:01:37.380
So, you have a stimulus type situation,

00:01:37.380 --> 00:01:40.390
or, in the intention where
you're turning the muscle on,

00:01:40.390 --> 00:01:42.330
turning it off, turning
it on, turning it off,

00:01:42.330 --> 00:01:45.590
it's a terrible stimulus.
You're not keeping

00:01:45.590 --> 00:01:46.950
constant tension on the muscle.

00:01:46.950 --> 00:01:50.030
So, they way to keep constant
tension on the muscle

00:01:50.030 --> 00:01:52.773
is instead of doing this,

00:01:53.770 --> 00:01:56.560
you do this.

00:01:56.560 --> 00:01:58.020
So, you see how the biceps

00:01:58.020 --> 00:02:00.410
that are very contracted position here,

00:02:00.410 --> 00:02:02.690
whereas here it's not at all.

00:02:02.690 --> 00:02:05.310
So, we get the highest tension,

00:02:05.310 --> 00:02:07.440
and the hardest contraction right here.

00:02:07.440 --> 00:02:09.000
So, the reason they call it drag curl

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:10.900
is 'cause, you're hovering the bar,

00:02:10.900 --> 00:02:13.820
kind of dragging it up
the front of your body.

00:02:13.820 --> 00:02:18.610
Now, as you do this, you're
engaging the posterior deltoid

00:02:18.610 --> 00:02:21.976
right back here, but
also your traps kind of,

00:02:21.976 --> 00:02:25.660
this muscle, the trapezius
kind of pushes your head

00:02:25.660 --> 00:02:30.460
a little forward, and that's
normal. Your normal positioning

00:02:30.460 --> 00:02:33.770
for a drag curl is the
head's going to come forward

00:02:33.770 --> 00:02:36.312
a little bit just
because the bio-mechanics

00:02:36.312 --> 00:02:41.312
require it to. Now, it
also turns the movement

00:02:41.415 --> 00:02:45.330
into a multi-joint movement,
and what we know from research

00:02:45.330 --> 00:02:49.153
is that multi-joint movements
stimulate more growth

00:02:49.153 --> 00:02:52.930
than single-joint movements.
So, by getting another joint

00:02:52.930 --> 00:02:56.370
involved, we're not only
really getting the posterior

00:02:56.370 --> 00:03:01.370
deltoid, we're enabling the
body to see two joints moving,

00:03:01.940 --> 00:03:04.680
maximizing the musculature
that could be involved.

00:03:04.680 --> 00:03:08.630
You're going to handle more
weight, and you're going to

00:03:08.630 --> 00:03:10.750
be able to stimulate more growth

00:03:10.750 --> 00:03:14.700
and have all the associate
benefits of a multi-joint

00:03:14.700 --> 00:03:17.543
movement and see incredible bicep growth.

